{"title_page": "Jim Jones and The Righteous Mind", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| background       = group_or_band\n| origin           = London, England\n| current_members  = Jim Jones<br/>Gavin Jay<br/>Matt Millership<br/>Mal Troon<br />Aidan Sinclair\n| image            = JJRM 3 by steve gullick.jpg\n| genre            = [[Rock n roll]],  [[psychedelic Rock]], [[Garage Punk]]. [[Blues]], [[Soul]],[[Country]]\n| label            = Ma\u00a7onic / [[Cargo Records]]<br/>Hound Gawd! Records<br />Raygun Records\n| past_members     = Henri Herbert<br />Joe Glossop<br />Phil Martini<br />David Page<br />Andy Marvell\n| associated_acts  = [[The Jim Jones Revue]]<br />[[Thee Hypnotics]]<br />[[Black Moses]]\n| website          = {{URL|http://righteousmind.co.uk}}\n}}\n\n'''Jim Jones and the Righteous Mind''' are a British [[Rock music|rock]] band formed in November 2014 by Jim Jones and Gavin Jay following the break-up of [[The Jim Jones Revue]]. The current line up includes pianist Matt Millership and multi-instrumentalist Mal Troon. \n\n<br />\n\n== History ==\nTaking their name from [[The Righteous Mind|a book on social psychology]], Jim Jones and the Righteous Mind came together after [[The Jim Jones Revue]] disbanded in 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.i94bar.com/news/jim-jones-breakup|title=Jim Jones Revue calls it a day {{!}} News|work=The I-94 Bar|access-date=2017-10-02|language=en-GB}}</ref> The band was initially composed of Jim Jones, Henri Herbert and Gavin Jay with [[Phil Martini]] on drums. Herbert left to concentrate on his burgeoning solo career<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://vivelerock.net/jim-jones-uncensored/|title=JIM JONES UNCENSORED! {{!}} Vive Le Rock Magazine|work=Vive Le Rock Magazine|access-date=2017-09-30|language=en-GB}}</ref> with Joe Glossop stepping in on keyboards. David Page joined on guitar / pedal steel and this line-up recorded the ''Boil Yer Blood EP'' and ''Aldecide'' for Raygun records. Due to touring commitments Glossop and Page were later replaced by Matt Millership and Mal Troon. \n\n0n 26 May 2017 the group released their debut album via their own imprint label Ma\u00a7onic on Hound Gawd! Records. The critically acclaimed<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/super-natural/jim-jones-the-righteous-mind|title=Metacritic reviews|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170515100814/http://www.metacritic.com/music/super-natural/jim-jones-the-righteous-mind|archive-date=2017-05-15|url-status=dead}}</ref> ''Super Natural'' was produced by Jim Jones and recorded in London at Space Eko East studio with Alex McGowan. French tattoo artist Jean-luc Navette designed the cover artwork for the album.\n\nTo support the release the band performed a live session for [http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b08prxmm Marc Riley on BBC6] and a live televised set in Paris for [http://www.canalplus.fr/musique/musique/pid5043-album-de-la-semaine.html ''Album De La Semaine''] on Canal+.\n\nIn 2018 the band announced a [[kickstarter]] campaign to fund their second album ''CollectiV'', which was again produced by Jim Jones and recorded at Space Eko East. Recording commenced in July of that year and featured guest appearances from [[Little Barrie]] Cadogan, Stuart Dace, Paul-Ronney Angel, Sister Cookie, Ray 'Sonic' Hanson, Alan Clayton, Vesna Petresin, Alex McGowan, Frank Dymore, Lucifire and Julian Marszalek. Andy Marvell played drums on the album and subsequent tours in the UK and Europe. Cover artwork was provided by Gavin Jay. Notably, a 1964 [[Gibson Hummingbird]] guitar belonging to [[Keith Richards]] was also used in the recording sessions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://planetradio.co.uk/planet-rock/news/rock-news/jim-jones-and-the-righteous-mind-detail-new-album-ft-keith-richards-guitar/|title=Jim Jones & The Righteous Mind detail new album ft. Keith Richards' guitar|website=Planet Rock|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>   \n\n''CollectiV'' was released on Ma\u00a7onic via [[Cargo Records]] on 8th March 2019 to positive reviews<ref>{{Citation|title=CollectiV by Jim Jones & Righteous Mind|url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/collectiv/jim-jones-righteous-mind|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>, [[Drowned In Sound]] declaring the record ''<nowiki/>'a masterclass in supremely executed rock and roll.''<nowiki/>'<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://drownedinsound.com/releases/20542/reviews/4152239|title=Album Review: Jim Jones and The Righteous Mind - CollectiV|website=DrownedInSound|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>   \n\n== Musical Style ==\nExpanding on the 1950s rock 'n' roll influences of [[The Jim Jones Revue]], The Righteous Mind has a darker, more cinematic sound incorporating [[Psychedelic rock|psychedelia]], country, blues and gospel, garnering favourable comparisons to [[Nick Cave and the Bad Seeds]], [[Tom Waits]] and [[The Stooges]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thequietus.com/articles/22383-jim-jones-righteous-mind-supernatural-album-review|title=The Quietus|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nComparing the two bands, The Quietus wrote that '<nowiki/>''...while the Jim Jones Revue swan-dived into rock & roll\u2019s primordial ooze with an unrestrained sense of glee and abandon, Jim Jones And The Righteous Mind is an exercise in intensity, dynamics and space that, while summoning up the feral excitement of the former outfit, delivers a satisfying and continuingly intriguing payload from a great height. This is less a case of being steamrollered and more of exploration, experimentation and execution''.'<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://thequietus.com/articles/22383-jim-jones-righteous-mind-supernatural-album-review|title=The Quietus {{!}} Reviews {{!}} Jim Jones & The Righteous Mind|work=The Quietus|access-date=2017-09-30}}</ref>  [http://recordcollectormag.com Record Collector] also noted that ''<nowiki/>'the Revue\u2019s sleaze-billy holler isn\u2019t abandoned so much as thickened on the riff\u2019n\u2019roll turmoil of his Righteous Mind debut'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://recordcollectormag.com/reviews/super-natural|title=Super Natural - Record Collector Magazine|website=recordcollectormag.com|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref> declaring the record ''<nowiki/>'ridiculously thrilling''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://recordcollectormag.com/reviews/super-natural|title=Super Natural - Record Collector Magazine|website=recordcollectormag.com|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref>' [[Vive Le Rock (magazine)|Vive Le Rock magazine]] awarded the album a 10/10 rating, writing 'T''here really aren't enough superlatives to describe just how good 'Super Natural' is - you'll be hard pushed to find anything near as perfect anywhere else all yea''r'<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mailchi.mp/6ab25274bbda/long-player-links-video-mayhem-french-tv?e=0c10f10c01|title=+++ LONG PLAYER LINKS +++ VIDEO MAYHEM +++ FRENCH TV +++|website=mailchi.mp|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref>\n\nThe musical guests on ''CollectiV'' helped broaden the sonic palette, adding [[Tenor saxophone|tenor]] and [[baritone saxophone]], [[bouzouki]] and [[Fender Bass VI]] to the mix of [[Pedal steel guitar|pedal steel]], [[Guitar|guitar,]] [[double bass]], organ, [[piano]] and [[Drum kit|drums]]. [[Louder Than War (website)|Louder Than War]] praised the '<nowiki/>''many moments of spectral, landscaped, beauty''<nowiki/>' alongside the '<nowiki/>''patented high octane rushes','' judging it an ''<nowiki/>'album of Rock 'n' roll from foot to the pedal raw rushes to dark introspective ballads distilled to perfection\u2019'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://louderthanwar.com/jim-jones-and-the-righteous-mind-collectiv-910-for-an-album-of-rock-n-roll-from-foot-to-the-pedal-raw-rushes-to-dark-introspective-ballads-distilled-to-perfection/|title=Jim Jones And The Righteous Mind 'CollectiV' : '9/10 for an album of perfect Rock n roll from foot to the pedal raw rushes to dark introspective ballads distilled to perfection\u2019|last=johnrobb|date=2019-03-02|website=Louder Than War|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> whilst Tinnitist noted ''<nowiki/>'they are still ready, willing and able to crash, bash and thrash an old-school groove-rocker at the drop of a gold medallion. But they\u2019re also unafraid to ease up on the throttle and venture into the subterranean realms of psyche-rock, twisted roots, hoodoo-voodoo and narcotized lounge balladry.'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tinnitist.com/2019/03/09/jim-jones-the-righteous-mind-collectiv/|title=Jim Jones & The Righteous Mind {{!}} CollectiV|last=Sterdan|first=Darryl|date=2019-03-09|website=Tinnitist|language=en-CA|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n=== Singles ===\n\n* ''Boil Yer Blood EP'' (2015), Raygun\n* ''Aldecide'' (2016), Raygun\n* ''Till Its All Gone'' (2016), Ma\u00a7onic\n* ''Heavy Lounge #1'' (2017), Ma\u00a7onic\n* ''Shazam'' (2018), Ma\u00a7onic\n*''Sex Robot'' (2019), Ma\u00a7onic\n*''Get Down Get With It'' (2019), Ma\u00a7onic\n\n=== Albums ===\n* ''[[Super Natural (album)|Super Natural]]'' LP (2017), Ma\u00a7onic / Hound Gawd! Records\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|1\n|Dream\n|4:34\n|-\n|2\n|Base Is Loaded\n|6:16\n|-\n|3\n|Something's Gonna Get Its Hands On You\n|4:53\n|-\n|4\n|No Fool\n|4:05\n|-\n|5\n|Aldecide\n|3:57\n|-\n|6\n|Boil Your Blood\n|3:24\n|-\n|7\n|Shallow Grave\n|5:08\n|-\n|8\n|Heavy Lounge #1\n|4:20\n|-\n|9\n|Till It's All Gone\n|4:48\n|-\n|10\n|Everybody But Me\n|5:39\n|}\n\n*''CollectiV'' LP (2019), Ma\u00a7onic / [[Cargo Records (UK)|Cargo Records]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|1\n|Sex Robot\n|3:06\n|-\n|2\n|Satan's Got His Heart Set On You             \n|3:32\n|-\n|3\n|O Genie\n|4:22\n|-\n|4\n|Attack Of The Killer Brainz\n|3:16\n|-\n|5\n|Meth Church\n|5:47\n|-\n|6\n|Dark Secrets\n|4:22\n|-\n|7\n|I Found A Love\n|3:10\n|-\n|8\n|Out Align\n|4:50\n|-\n|9\n|Going There Anyway\n|3:35\n|-\n|10\n|Shazam\n|3:49\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.righteousmind.co.uk/}}\n* [https://www.facebook.com/jjatrm/ Facebook]\n* [https://twitter.com/JJandtheRM Twitter]\n* [http://www.houndgawd.com/shop/en/home/ Hound Gawd! Records]\n\n[[Category:2014 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:British rock music groups]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| background       = group_or_band\n| origin           = London, England\n| current_members  = Jim Jones<br/>Gavin Jay<br/>Matt Millership<br/>Mal Troon<br />Aidan Sinclair\n| image            = JJRM 3 by steve gullick.jpg\n| genre            = [[Rock n roll]],  [[psychedelic Rock]], [[Garage Punk]]. [[Blues]], [[Soul]],[[Country]]\n| label            = Ma\u00a7onic / [[Cargo Records]]<br/>Hound Gawd! Records<br />Raygun Records\n| past_members     = Henri Herbert<br />Joe Glossop<br />Phil Martini<br />David Page<br />Andy Marvell\n| associated_acts  = [[The Jim Jones Revue]]<br />[[Thee Hypnotics]]<br />[[Black Moses]]\n| website          = {{URL|http://righteousmind.co.uk}}\n}}\n\n'''Jim Jones and the Righteous Mind''' are a British [[Rock music|rock]] band formed in November 2014 by Jim Jones and Gavin Jay following the break-up of [[The Jim Jones Revue]]. \n\n<br />\n\n== History ==\nTaking their name from [[The Righteous Mind|a book on social psychology]], Jim Jones and the Righteous Mind came together following the break-up of [[The Jim Jones Revue]] in 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.i94bar.com/news/jim-jones-breakup|title=Jim Jones Revue calls it a day {{!}} News|work=The I-94 Bar|access-date=2017-10-02|language=en-GB}}</ref> The band was initially composed of Jim Jones, Henri Herbert and Gavin Jay with [[Phil Martini]] on drums. Herbert left to concentrate on his burgeoning solo career<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://vivelerock.net/jim-jones-uncensored/|title=JIM JONES UNCENSORED! {{!}} Vive Le Rock Magazine|work=Vive Le Rock Magazine|access-date=2017-09-30|language=en-GB}}</ref> with Joe Glossop stepping in on keyboards. David Page joined on guitar / pedal steel and this line-up recorded the ''Boil Yer Blood EP'' and ''Aldecide'' for Raygun records. Due to touring commitments Glossop and Page were later replaced by Matt Millership and Mal Troon. \n\n0n 26 May 2017 the group released their debut album via their own imprint label Ma\u00a7onic on Hound Gawd! Records. The critically acclaimed<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/super-natural/jim-jones-the-righteous-mind|title=Metacritic reviews|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170515100814/http://www.metacritic.com/music/super-natural/jim-jones-the-righteous-mind|archive-date=2017-05-15|url-status=dead}}</ref> ''Super Natural'' was produced by Jim Jones and recorded in London at Space Eko East studio with Alex McGowan. French tattoo artist Jean-luc Navette designed the cover artwork for the album.\n\nTo support the release the band performed a live session for [http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b08prxmm Marc Riley on BBC6] and a live televised set in Paris for [http://www.canalplus.fr/musique/musique/pid5043-album-de-la-semaine.html ''Album De La Semaine''] on Canal+.\n\nIn 2018 the band announced a [[kickstarter]] campaign to fund their second album ''CollectiV'', which was again produced by Jim Jones and recorded at Space Eko East. Recording commenced in July of that year and featured guest appearances from [[Little Barrie]] Cadogan, Stuart Dace, Paul-Ronney Angel, Sister Cookie, Ray 'Sonic' Hanson, Alan Clayton, Vesna Petresin, Alex McGowan, Frank Dymore, Lucifire and Julian Marszalek. Andy Marvell played drums on the album and subsequent tours in the UK and Europe. Cover artwork was provided by Gavin Jay. Notably, a 1964 [[Gibson Hummingbird]] guitar belonging to [[Keith Richards]] was also used in the recording sessions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://planetradio.co.uk/planet-rock/news/rock-news/jim-jones-and-the-righteous-mind-detail-new-album-ft-keith-richards-guitar/|title=Jim Jones & The Righteous Mind detail new album ft. Keith Richards' guitar|website=Planet Rock|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>   \n\n''CollectiV'' was released on Ma\u00a7onic via [[Cargo Records]] on 8th March 2019 to positive reviews<ref>{{Citation|title=CollectiV by Jim Jones & Righteous Mind|url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/collectiv/jim-jones-righteous-mind|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>, [[Drowned In Sound]] declaring the record ''<nowiki/>'a masterclass in supremely executed rock and roll.''<nowiki/>'<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://drownedinsound.com/releases/20542/reviews/4152239|title=Album Review: Jim Jones and The Righteous Mind - CollectiV|website=DrownedInSound|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>   \n\n== Musical Style ==\nExpanding on the 1950s rock 'n' roll influences of [[The Jim Jones Revue]], The Righteous Mind has a darker, more cinematic sound incorporating [[Psychedelic rock|psychedelia]], country, blues and gospel, garnering favourable comparisons to [[Nick Cave and the Bad Seeds]], [[Tom Waits]] and [[The Stooges]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thequietus.com/articles/22383-jim-jones-righteous-mind-supernatural-album-review|title=The Quietus|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nComparing the two bands, The Quietus wrote that '<nowiki/>''...while the Jim Jones Revue swan-dived into rock & roll\u2019s primordial ooze with an unrestrained sense of glee and abandon, Jim Jones And The Righteous Mind is an exercise in intensity, dynamics and space that, while summoning up the feral excitement of the former outfit, delivers a satisfying and continuingly intriguing payload from a great height. This is less a case of being steamrollered and more of exploration, experimentation and execution''.'<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://thequietus.com/articles/22383-jim-jones-righteous-mind-supernatural-album-review|title=The Quietus {{!}} Reviews {{!}} Jim Jones & The Righteous Mind|work=The Quietus|access-date=2017-09-30}}</ref>  [http://recordcollectormag.com Record Collector] also noted that ''<nowiki/>'the Revue\u2019s sleaze-billy holler isn\u2019t abandoned so much as thickened on the riff\u2019n\u2019roll turmoil of his Righteous Mind debut'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://recordcollectormag.com/reviews/super-natural|title=Super Natural - Record Collector Magazine|website=recordcollectormag.com|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref> declaring the record ''<nowiki/>'ridiculously thrilling''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://recordcollectormag.com/reviews/super-natural|title=Super Natural - Record Collector Magazine|website=recordcollectormag.com|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref>' [[Vive Le Rock (magazine)|Vive Le Rock magazine]] awarded the album a 10/10 rating, writing 'T''here really aren't enough superlatives to describe just how good 'Super Natural' is - you'll be hard pushed to find anything near as perfect anywhere else all yea''r'<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mailchi.mp/6ab25274bbda/long-player-links-video-mayhem-french-tv?e=0c10f10c01|title=+++ LONG PLAYER LINKS +++ VIDEO MAYHEM +++ FRENCH TV +++|website=mailchi.mp|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref>\n\nThe musical guests on ''CollectiV'' helped broaden the sonic palette, adding [[Tenor saxophone|tenor]] and [[baritone saxophone]], [[bouzouki]] and [[Fender Bass VI]] to the mix of [[Pedal steel guitar|pedal steel]], [[Guitar|guitar,]] [[double bass]], organ, [[piano]] and [[Drum kit|drums]]. [[Louder Than War (website)|Louder Than War]] praised the '<nowiki/>''many moments of spectral, landscaped, beauty''<nowiki/>' alongside the '<nowiki/>''patented high octane rushes','' judging it an ''<nowiki/>'album of Rock 'n' roll from foot to the pedal raw rushes to dark introspective ballads distilled to perfection\u2019'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://louderthanwar.com/jim-jones-and-the-righteous-mind-collectiv-910-for-an-album-of-rock-n-roll-from-foot-to-the-pedal-raw-rushes-to-dark-introspective-ballads-distilled-to-perfection/|title=Jim Jones And The Righteous Mind 'CollectiV' : '9/10 for an album of perfect Rock n roll from foot to the pedal raw rushes to dark introspective ballads distilled to perfection\u2019|last=johnrobb|date=2019-03-02|website=Louder Than War|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> whilst Tinnitist noted ''<nowiki/>'they are still ready, willing and able to crash, bash and thrash an old-school groove-rocker at the drop of a gold medallion. But they\u2019re also unafraid to ease up on the throttle and venture into the subterranean realms of psyche-rock, twisted roots, hoodoo-voodoo and narcotized lounge balladry.'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tinnitist.com/2019/03/09/jim-jones-the-righteous-mind-collectiv/|title=Jim Jones & The Righteous Mind {{!}} CollectiV|last=Sterdan|first=Darryl|date=2019-03-09|website=Tinnitist|language=en-CA|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n=== Singles ===\n\n* ''Boil Yer Blood EP'' (2015), Raygun\n* ''Aldecide'' (2016), Raygun\n* ''Till Its All Gone'' (2016), Ma\u00a7onic\n* ''Heavy Lounge #1'' (2017), Ma\u00a7onic\n* ''Shazam'' (2018), Ma\u00a7onic\n*''Sex Robot'' (2019), Ma\u00a7onic\n*''Get Down Get With It'' (2019), Ma\u00a7onic\n\n=== Albums ===\n* ''[[Super Natural (album)|Super Natural]]'' LP (2017), Ma\u00a7onic / Hound Gawd! Records\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|1\n|Dream\n|4:34\n|-\n|2\n|Base Is Loaded\n|6:16\n|-\n|3\n|Something's Gonna Get Its Hands On You\n|4:53\n|-\n|4\n|No Fool\n|4:05\n|-\n|5\n|Aldecide\n|3:57\n|-\n|6\n|Boil Your Blood\n|3:24\n|-\n|7\n|Shallow Grave\n|5:08\n|-\n|8\n|Heavy Lounge #1\n|4:20\n|-\n|9\n|Till It's All Gone\n|4:48\n|-\n|10\n|Everybody But Me\n|5:39\n|}\n\n*''CollectiV'' LP (2019), Ma\u00a7onic / [[Cargo Records (UK)|Cargo Records]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|1\n|Sex Robot\n|3:06\n|-\n|2\n|Satan's Got His Heart Set On You             \n|3:32\n|-\n|3\n|O Genie\n|4:22\n|-\n|4\n|Attack Of The Killer Brainz\n|3:16\n|-\n|5\n|Meth Church\n|5:47\n|-\n|6\n|Dark Secrets\n|4:22\n|-\n|7\n|I Found A Love\n|3:10\n|-\n|8\n|Out Align\n|4:50\n|-\n|9\n|Going There Anyway\n|3:35\n|-\n|10\n|Shazam\n|3:49\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{